This paper proposes a machine learning approach for financial forecasting, specifically for stock time series forecasting. The paper uses a multi-task learning framework to process multiple time series of related stocks simultaneously, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an attention method based on the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM), which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with financial data, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.CE (Computational Economics and Finance) sub-category. The use of multiple networks and attention methods also suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with forecasting, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
